node.label: A Pacemaker user should be able to - Track and log activities - Obtain progress reports on their activities - Have prescribed workouts based on previous activities - Connect with firends and compare workouts with friends
All the Analytic Data is calculated on the fly via the Android App and is not stored. Only the activities are stored and the calculations are based on the activities
All data is stored in the MySQL database. The Android App communicates via REST with the Website to load and store objects

The Webserver is ran off a raspberry pi (Play Application) with the MySQL database also being on the same raspberry pi - not overly modular however cost effective for a college project. Previously had an RDS instance for the database, 2 servers for the application and a load balancer all on AWS but this is no longer cost effective
